<Content>Just OK The hotel was tucked away in a quiet area of Barcelona in the financial area. A five-10 minute walk to the nearest Metro and Bus Turistic stops. The rooms were neat and clean. The free continental breakfast was OK. What I was most annoyed with was the blase attitude of some of the staff. Depending on who was at the desk, service or questions about the city could be like a trip to the dentist. They did not go out of the way to offer advice. Also, don't look for restaurants near the hotel. Most better places are located in more lively parts of town. The best part was the hotel had a reasonable price. Pre booked at $205 per night. 
