<Author>magnapig
<Content>Watch out for the cost of breakfast! We were booked in by a promoter for two nights. The hotel was pleasant and the staff seemed nice enough.The first morning we went to breakfast..There was no sign to say that it was a buffet costing Euro15, and there was no alternative menu, so I assumed that the breakfast was included in the price of the room. I had a cup of tea. The 2nd morning I had a cup of tea and a slice of toast.When we went to check out we found that breakfast was not included and so my two cups of tea and slice of toast cost the promoter Euro 30.I tried to argue the point with the desk manager, but he was extremely rude and unhelpful, as was the other man on the desk.In the end we were going to be late for our flight home and had to drop the matter.I have stayed in hotels all over the world and have never come across such rudeness. Neither have I ever known any hotel not make it clear, or offer an alternative menu, when breakfast is not included in the price of the room. 
