<Content>definately 2 star 2 friends and myself stayed for a week at this hotel, check in was straightforward, however we were not made aware that we should pay a 20 euro deposit to obtain a remote control for the aircon, therefore thinking that it was just broken suffered for almost 3 days in sweltering heat, until a friend we had made on holiday put the aircon on 4 us using her remote, we had reported a failure to the reception, no one came to fix it and still no one told us we needed the control. our bathroom door locked itself and it took maintenance 2 hours to come open it for us. however the rooms were clean and the maid service was excellent.the food was terrible, you could get an english breakfast, but most of the food was cold, and the spanish guests pushed in front of other people which i found very rude. anyone could walk in off the streets and eat in the restaraunt because there was only someone checking your room keys on admission 3 times in the week we stayed. the bar staff were either miserable or trying it on us which made it uncomfortable going to get a drink.the location was ok, but the bins by mcdonalds did stink.thank goodness the weather was great. 
