<Author>ksite
<Content>Great hotel, not so great service This hotel would have got a 4, or even a 5 had it not been for our experience on the last day. On the final morning I requested to book a taxi for later that day. The receptionist said that would be no problem - just contact them about 15 minutes before we were due to leave and they would call for one.When we went to leave the hotel at 3.30pm we requested the hotel called a taxi to take us to the airport. A different receptionist said there would be plenty on the road outside and to just flag one down. After 20 minutes standing outside in the rain trying to hail a taxi we returned and asked the hotel to phone for a taxi. A combination of rain and siesta time meant vacant taxis were fairly low on the ground.The receptionist refused! He said the taxi number would 'probably' be engaged so it wasn't worth trying and that we would be able to flag one down quicker. I explained that I'd already waited on the main road for 20 minutes, and insisted he at least try and phone a taxi for us. He would not budge and was extremely rude in his manner.For any hotel, let alone 4 star, I find this level of service totally unacceptable. If it weren't for time constraints (we had a plane to catch) I would have pursued the matter with the manager. Luckily a further 10 minutes in the rain saw a taxi finally displaying a green light.As I said above, had this incident not happened, I would have awarded the hotel a 4 or a 5. The location was excellent, just outside the main hub of the city, but well within walking distance of the main attractions, with the tube 5 minutes away when we didn;t feel like walking.The room was spacious enough, and immaculate throughout - and the maids daily visit ensured it stayed that way.Breakfast was better than average on the Continent with a buffet including hot food as well as the traditional cold meat and cheeses.I would stay again, but would insist on the morning of departure that a taxi is booked. 
