<Content>OK Hotel with Good Access My wife and I spent four nights at the Balmoral in September 2004. It is a few steps from Calle Diagonal, a main street through Barcelona that gives you access to buses and a few blocks from the Diagonal Metro stop at Rambla Catalunya. It is a Four Star Occidental hotel, but the rooms we had were pequeno (small) and located on the center court-yard, which in this case was the neighborhood backyards. Actually, not a bad room because the Via Augusta has some traffic during the day. Our room was quiet and had a window that opened. The facilities, although clean, were small and oversold on their website. The desk is relatively efficient, but there is no concierge, and one desk person refused to confirm flights and transfers to the airport. English was not a problem, but I speak some Spanish and made myself undestood when necessary.The restaurant on the evening we stayed for dinner was not particularly good, as there were few selections left, and our entrees were barely edible. Other restaurants in the area are superior.We would have reservations about staying there again. 
