<Content>Quiet and Close to All in the City The Balmoral Hotel on Avenue Augusta is right off Avenue Diagonal and close to the bus stop that takes you to the Forum (Balmes-Paris) and also close to Avenue Gracia which has the Tourist Bus routes - both red and blue. The hotel was quiet and some rooms have small balconies. The hot buffet breakfast was convenient.The main drawback was lots of cigarette smoke every where you went in Barcelona, however, non-smoking laws go into effect December 31, 2004, to give us a little more clean air.One other drawback is that there is a peculiar odor in the air at times in Barcelona (sewage?) due to some of the city being built on reclaimed land. Perhaps it is better in cooler weather 
